# File southern_midlatitude_SON.amc - generic southern midlatitude atmosphere, SON average.
#
# The profiles in this file were derived from NASA MERRA2 reanalysis
# data, temporally and spatially averaged using the Giovanni online
# data system developed and maintained by the NASA Goddard Earth
# Sciences Data and Information Services Center (GES DISC).
#
# Files:
#   g4.curtainTime.M2IMNPASM_5_12_4_H.20061201-20161130.180W_66S_180E_23S.nc
#   g4.curtainTime.M2IMNPASM_5_12_4_O3.20061201-20161130.180W_66S_180E_23S.nc
#   g4.curtainTime.M2IMNPASM_5_12_4_QV.20061201-20161130.180W_66S_180E_23S.nc
#   g4.curtainTime.M2IMNPASM_5_12_4_T.20061201-20161130.180W_66S_180E_23S.nc
#
# MERRA references:
#   M. M. Rienecker et al. (2011), MERRA: NASA's Modern-Era Retrospective
#   Analysis for Research and Applications. J. Climate 24:3624.
#
#   A. Molod et al (2015), Development of the GEOS-5 atmospheric general
#   circulation model: evolution from MERRA to MERRA2.  Geoscience Model
#   Development 8:1339. 
#
# MERRA is produced by the NASA/Goddard Global Modeling and Assimilation
# Office (GMAO).  MERRA data are archived and distributed by the
# GES DISC.
?
? Usage:
?  am southern_midlatitude_SON.amc  f_min  f_max  df  zenith_angle  trop_h2o_scale_factor
?
? Example:
?  am southern_midlatitude_SON.amc  0 GHz  300 GHz  10 MHz  0 deg  1.0
?
f %1 %2  %3 %4  %5 %6
output f GHz  tx  Tb K
za %7 %8
tol 1e-4

Nscale troposphere h2o %9

T0 2.7 K

layer mesosphere
Pbase 0.1 mbar   # z = 64260 m
Tbase 224.5 K
lineshape Voigt-Kielkopf
column dry_air vmr
column h2o vmr 5.93e-06
column o3 vmr 1.57e-06

